                                p#narrate-2-types-3  
                                    span The initial contact from the scammer will often come late at night when people may be disoriented or less alert, making them more vulnerable to being confused or misled.
                                p#narrate-3-types-3 
                                    span Scammers may reach out during times of bad weather, natural disasters, or other concerning events when people are already in a heightened state of worry about their loved ones' safety. This preys on the grandparentsâ€™ emotional vulnerability.   
