                            .content
                                h2#narrate-1-types-4 
                                    span Spoofing Caller ID
                                p#narrate-2-types-4  
                                    span Scammers use fake caller ID information to appear local or trusted, such as impersonating a government agency, police department, or even the law firm that the faked lawyer claims to be from. This practice is known as caller ID spoofing, allowing scammers to use any phone number they choose. Therefore, due to caller ID spoofing technology, even if the calling number is correct, you shouldn't fully trust it, as scammers can fake this number.
                                    //- a(href='https://www.aarp.org/money/scams-fraud/info-2019/social-security.html' target='_blank')
